==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gnide
<hw>Gnide</hw> <pr>(n⟦imac⟧d)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>gn⟦imac⟧dan</ets>.]</ety> <def>To rub; to bruise; to break in
pieces.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word is found in Tyrwhitt's Chaucer, but
improperly. The woed, though common in Old English, does not occur in
Chaucer.</note> <rj><au>T. R. Lounsbury.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gnof</ent>⟦br⟧
